As an AI language model, I don't have personal preferences or emotions. However, I can suggest some famous and generally acclaimed poems that might interest you:

1. "The Waste Land" by T.S. Eliot
2. "Howl" by Allen Ginsberg
3. "Do Not Go Gentle Into That Good Night" by Dylan Thomas
4. "The Love Song of J. Alfred Prufrock" by T.S. Eliot
5. "The Road Not Taken" by Robert Frost
6. "I Wandered Lonely as a Cloud" by William Wordsworth
7. "Sonnet 18" by William Shakespeare
8. "Ode to a Nightingale" by John Keats
9. "Annabel Lee" by Edgar Allan Poe
10. "Stopping by Woods on a Snowy Evening" by Robert Frost.

Of course, everyone has different tastes in poetry, so these are just a few suggestions to get you started.
